  JOHANNESBURG - World-renowned director Martin Scorsese is at it again, with another epic gangster film, The Irishman. Veterans Robert de Niro and Al Pacino stars. The two are famous for working in similar genres and have also teamed up on screen before. The film is based on former investigator and writer, Charles Brandt’s memoirs, 'I Heard You Paint Houses'. It reflects on the life and career of a hitman Frank, 'The Irishman' Sheeran, played by De Niro. It also delves into the disappearance of union leader Jimmy Hoffa. The film hits the big screen on 1 November and Netflix on 27 November.